The length of each vector can be calculated as follows:

$$
\begin{aligned}
l_1 &= \sqrt{k^2 + 1^2 + 1^2} \\
l_2 &= \sqrt{1^2 + k^2 + 1^2} \\
l_3 &= \sqrt{1^2 + 1^2 + k^2}
\end{aligned}
$$

The angle between the vectors can be calculated as follows:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\theta &= \arccos \left( \frac{l_2^2 - l_1^2}{2 l_1 l_2} \right) \\
&= \arccos \left( \frac{1^2 + k^2 + 1^2 - (k^2 + 1^2)}{2 (1^2 + k^2 + 1^2)} \right) \\
&= \arccos \left( \frac{2}{3} \right) \\
&= \frac{\pi}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the values of $k$ for which the angle between the vectors $\begin{pmatrix} k \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ k \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ is $\frac{\pi}{3}$ are $k = \pm \sqrt{3}$.

