-ay + bz + cz &= d \\
-ay - bz + cz &= d
\end{align*}
Solving this system, we get
\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{d}{2a} \pm \frac{1}{2a} \sqrt{4a^2 - d^2} \\
y &= \frac{d}{2b} \pm \frac{1}{2b} \sqrt{4b^2 - d^2} \\
z &= \frac{d}{2c} \pm \frac{1}{2c} \sqrt{4c^2 - d^2}
\end{align*}
Therefore, the normal vector of plane $P$ is given by
\begin{align*}
\begin{pmatrix} a \\ b \\ c \end{pmatrix} &= \frac{d}{2a} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \pm \frac{1}{2a} \sqrt{4a^2 - d^2} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \frac{d}{2a} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \pm \frac{1}{2a} \sqrt{4a^2 - d^2} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \frac{d}{2a} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \pm \frac{1}{2a} \sqrt{4a^2 - d^2} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
where the last equality follows from the fact that the square root of a negative number is not defined.

