For what ordered pair $(a,b)$ are there infinite solutions $(x,y)$ to the system \begin{align*}
2ax+2y&=b,\\
5x+y&=-3?
\end{align*}

model_outputs.model_answer:
The system of equations can be rewritten as:

\begin{align*}
2ax+2y&=b\\
5x+y&=-3\\
x^2+y^2&=1
\end{align*}

Solving the system of equations, we get:

\begin{align*}
x&= \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4 a c}}{2 a} \\
y&= \frac{-3 \pm \sqrt{9^2-4 \cdot 5 c}}{2 \cdot 5}
\end{align*}

where $c=1$.

Therefore, there are infinite solutions $(x,y)$ to the system of equations, where $x,y \in \mathbb{R}$.

